10/06/2010
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- US Brigadier General David Enyeart assumed command of NATO headquarters in Sarajevo on Wednesday (June 9th) from Brigadier General John Bullard.
At the ceremony, Enyeart said that the Alliance will continue to support BiH's Defence Ministry and armed forces.
In his farewell speech, Bullard praised the country's progress in reforming its defence sector.
NATO Commander of Allied Joint Force Command Naples Admiral Mark Fitzgerald -- as well as other senior military and civilian officials -- attended the ceremony at Camp Butmir.
(BHRT, Dnevni Avaz, RTS, Fena - 09/06/10)
